  "description": "<i>Shiloh 1862</i> is a 1-player strategy game for the 8-bit Atari computer.<br><br>This is a brigade level one-player simulation of the first day of the Battle of Shiloh during the American Civil War.  The player directs movement and bombardment of the Union Army against the computer controlled Confederate Army.  <br><br>The player controls all movements via the joystick, and each turn directs the movement of each of his units.  The computer then takes a turn with all movements.  The player wins by preventing the Confederate Army from occupying Pittsburg Landing.  ",
